---
title: 'Results for age-specific/mobility renewal model'
output:
  html_document: 
    default
params:
  stanModelFile:
    value: x
  job_dir:
    value: x
  states:
    value: x
  JOBID:
    value: x
---

```{r setup, include=FALSE}
library(knitr)
opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE)
```

```{r, include=FALSE}
args = params
file.to.figure = function(name) file.path(args$job_dir, 'figure',  paste0(args$stanModelFile, "-",args$JOBID, "-", name, ".png"))
file.to.table = function(name) file.path(args$job_dir, 'table', paste0(args$stanModelFile, "-",args$JOBID, "-", name, ".rds"))
```

## Session info
This file presents the results of Stan model 
```{r, echo=FALSE}
args$stanModelFile
```
with jobid
```{r, echo=FALSE}
args$JOBID
```

## Results

## Convergence diagnostics {.tabset .tabset-fade}

`r if ('AL' %in% args$states) '### Alabama'`

#### Effective sample size
Listed below are the parameters with an effective sample size smaller than 500.

```{r, include=('AL' %in% args$states), out.width="120%", fig.show='hold', fig.align='centre', echo=FALSE}
if(file.exists(file.to.table("eff_sample_size_cum_AL"))){
  neff <- readRDS(file.to.table("eff_sample_size_cum_AL"))
  neff[which(neff<500)]
}
```

#### Number of divergence and treedepth

```{r, include=('AL' %in% args$states), out.width="120%", fig.show='hold', fig.align='centre', echo=FALSE}
if(file.exists(file.to.table("diagnostics_AL"))){
  tmp <- readRDS(file.to.table("diagnostics_AL"))
  matrix(c('divergences', 'treedepth', tmp[[1]], tmp[[2]]), nrow = 2, ncol = 2, byrow = T)
}
```

#### WAIC
```{r, include=('AL' %in% args$states), out.width="120%", fig.show='hold', fig.align='centre', echo=FALSE}
if(file.exists(file.to.table("WAIC_AL"))){
  apply(readRDS(file.to.table("WAIC_AL")), 2, sum)
}
```

#### LOO
```{r, include=('AL' %in% args$states), out.width="120%", fig.show='hold', fig.align='centre', echo=FALSE}
if(file.exists(file.to.table("LOO_AL"))){
  apply(readRDS(file.to.table("LOO_AL")), 2, sum)
}
```
